---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navigation from "../../components/Navigation.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="Lessons From Building DailyDine">
  <Navigation />

  <main id="main-content" class="flex-1 max-w-[68ch] mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-24 flex flex-col gap-12 font-sans">
    
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4">
      <div class="flex gap-2 text-xs text-[#71717A] font-mono">
        <span>Engineering Log</span>
        <span>·</span>
        <span>July 2026</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-display font-medium text-[#FAFAFA] tracking-tight leading-tight">
        Lessons From Building DailyDine
      </h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[#A1A1AA] italic">
        "Favor simple structures over distributed state machines."
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Article Content -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-8 text-[#FAFAFA] text-base leading-[1.7] tracking-tight font-normal">
      <p>
        During the development of DailyDine's scheduling API, we ran into classic concurrency problems.
        When booking system locks are handled in application code instead of database boundaries,
        concurrent web requests can easily cause race conditions and duplicate reservations.
      </p>
      
      <p>
        We initially tried to coordinate this with a Redis lock mechanism.
        However, managing key expiries, network drops, and cleanup scripts added too much complexity.
        We deleted the Redis coordination layer entirely and moved constraints directly to PostgreSQL.
        Using PostgreSQL exclusion constraints resolved scheduling conflicts with zero application overhead.
      </p>

      <p>
        The biggest lesson is that over-engineering early in development is a trap.
        WebSockets and cache layers look modern, but relational databases with transactional isolates
        are almost always the most reliable solution.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Article Footer -->
    <footer class="flex flex-col gap-8 border-t border-[rgba(255,255,255,0.06)] pt-12 mt-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-8 text-sm">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
          <h4 class="text-xs text-[#71717A] uppercase tracking-wider font-medium font-mono">Case Study Details</h4>
          <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2">
            <li>
              <a href="/work/dailydine" class="text-[#2563EB] hover:underline">
                Read DailyDine Case Study
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>

  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
